Rapid City.name: Coffee and the Cats
Rapid City.address: 315 B E Saint Patrick St, Rapid City, SD 57701, USA

text.text: We miss our pets that have moved on. Moving into a place that doesn't allow pets,  this establishment is just what we need to get our furry critters fix. They also have excellent refreshments that you may desire. It's recommended to put in a reservation for the kitty room.

This place is the best. Noah was really kind and made me an awesome latte. The French macarons were excellent. Inside is so cozy and beautifully decorated. And they take care of cats and help them get adopted! You can spend 30mins in the cat room for just $5 ü•∞üêà‚ú®

I‚Äôd been hearing about this place for some time through Facebook chatter and I decided to come check it out. I wasn‚Äôt exactly sure what to expect. It was a cold and foggy day, so a piping hot coffee and snack seemed like a good idea. We set out to Coffee and Cats for our first experience. The store is on Saint Patrick‚Äôs street just, next to a daycare and across the street from Calvary Church. As we approached I could see a little sign in the window displaying an artistic rendition of a cat with the words ‚ÄúCoffee, Because Murdered is Wrong‚Äù.  I burst out laughing because I happen to love cats, and the depiction was purrfect. Teaching one of the Ten Commandments across the street from a church using cats and coffee to get the point across seemed oddly appropriate.

In we go to a very cozy atmosphere, with cool ceiling tiles, plush couches, eclectic wall art and an ample supply of coffee flavors abound. Steam is rising through the air out of a nicely equipped coffee machine. From around it comes one of the owners to welcome us in. Very nicely done. Each choice is cat-related and I decided to go simple. I got the Siamese (Vanilla and Cinnamon) and our second was the hot coco (with marshmallow and graham cracker). After placing our order we had time to look at the delectable offerings in the glass case.

Cookies, pastries and fun stuff like the jiggly kitty infused with a flavored tea and milk. I got one of those too. It was a hard choice I must admit.

We opted to see the cats and made a donation. The cats are in an enclosure with clear windows so you can watch them play on the many obstacle courses inside. The entire store is very clean and well kept. I was wondering how you mix cats and coffee and now I had the answer. Both coffee and coco were amazing. The little jiggly kitty not only tasted great, but provided quite a bit of entertainment before taking the spoon to split its head open. I didn‚Äôt feel bad at all.

Once we were finished it was time to see the cats. We were guided over to the door, given friendly and clear instructions, provided sanitizer and sprayed our shoes before entering. We were greeted by some friendly cats who wanted attention and others that simply stayed where they were. All-around it was fun. We didn‚Äôt end up taking a cat home, but that‚Äôs not required and it was really enjoyable!

The owners are three young adults. I‚Äôm not sure of their age, but it was impressive to see entrepreneurial endeavors such as this with our youth. Way to go!

It‚Äôs worth it to take a drive over here and support such a cool place, great owners and a unique concept with wonderful coffee, coco, pastries and cats to entertain. I encourage you to support them and I intend to go back again, especially during the winter months when I feel like a sweet, a coffee, great service and a few cats to look and laugh with.

Congrats on your business and count me in as a customer and cheerleader for you guys!

Seattle.name: NEKO Cat Cafe Seattle
Seattle.address: 519 E Pine St, Seattle, WA 98122, USA

text.text: This was such a great experience! we were in Seattle traveling for the week and missing our cats at home, so we decided to pop in for a visit! $25 for a 45 minute session with the cutest, sweetest, cats in Seattle! I definitely recommend coming here as the fee goes to a good cause, and you get a great experience out of it. It‚Äôs very clear that these cats are loved and well taken care of! I also recommend the Fez Mint Tea! It was delicious on that cold Seattle night. :)

I booked an appointment in advance to visit the Neko kitties. The staff was friendly and it was nice to have drinks and snacks available. The visit was 45 minutes long and time was shared with 8-10 cats and a few other people who had booked. I loved the cats even if many of them were ready for naps during our visit. Some of the cats are residents while others are available for adoption. Staff wipe down the space between visits. Well run cafe!  I'd love to go back if I'm ever back in Seattle!

Great experience. I had visited once before in passing for a beverage and a peek at the kitties, but I'm happy to have been able to book a visit with the kitties this time around. It was definitely worth it! Be sure to check out the sweet pickles collar bow ties if you're looking to spice up your own kitty's wardrobe.

Fun little experience! Pleasant staff, clean atmosphere, aloof cats. I made a mistake when booking tickets. I called them, and the nice young woman who answered was able to quickly fix my mistake. The experience was lovely and sweet. I'd recommend this for neurodivergent people who don't want to be overstimulated.

My fianc√© and I went for a day trip from Canada to the US and he brought me to the Neko Cat Cafe! We were very excited for the experience. When arriving, I could see how much they care for the cats; it almost felt like the cats ran the cafe and the employees were just there to feed them :D I was very pleased with how clean the environment was and how cat friendly everything was. They also serve alcohol and nonalcoholic beverages which was a bonus!

Simon will forever be in my heart!
I love all the kitties! Luna, Prairie, Tilly, and Freya have all sat in my lap! The cats are all really chill, and super funny.

Roseville.name: The Cafe Meow
Roseville.address: 1718A Lexington Ave N, Roseville, MN 55113, USA

text.text: I had such a great time at this place! There are games, books, fun products to buy (I left with multiple things), GREAT coffee, and cute cats. The staff is wonderful. I highly recommend this place! You DO need to make a reservation online if you‚Äôd like to visit the area with the cats. It is so worth it!

I love to grab a coffee and play with kittens for an hour to forget that we still have 9 more months of winter. Just make sure you get a reservation because they‚Äôre popular! The kitties are well cared for by a staff who do a great job at keeping everyone safe and happy.
Super friendly staff and they really care about the cats here. I loved my time interacting with the cats. They were all so cute and playful at 11am.

Harrisonburg.name: Aristocat Cafe + Tea House
Harrisonburg.address: 111 N Liberty St, Harrisonburg, VA 22802, USA

text.text: I have been to this coffee shop two times and it has been an extremely delightful experience every time! Their matcha latte was one of the best I‚Äôve ever had, and their oat milk vanilla latte was equally delicious. Both times I‚Äôve went I also visited the cat lounge, you can tell the cats are very well taken care of and $15 for an hour is such a great price. Not only are the cats super cute but the money will help with their care! Will definitely be one of the coffee shops I‚Äôll be visiting regularly.

We went to celebrate my daughter's birthday and had the best time. Coffee and hot chocolate was delicious, with a ton of options for drinks and snacks. It was impeccably clean, including the cat area. Such a cool set up and the cats were adorable. Had a great chat with the owner and both she and the staff were warm and kind. We will definitely return. The best day with great memories made!
This was so fun! So clean (I have severe allergies) and it only affected me a little bit. The treats were delicious and the kitties was so great. Awesome service!

Reno.name: Kitty Kisses Cat Caf√©
Reno.address: 8555 Double R Blvd Suite 104, Reno, NV 89511, USA

text.text:
We originally had a very good experience and shared super positive things on Google and social media. I even had people in the Reno/Tahoe area reach out about adopting from this cafe and rescue and I gave them a rave review about our experience here. However, a few hours after our visit we noticed an extra charge to our bank account. We were charged an additional $10.00 for apparently breaking the rules. When I asked what rules were broken, I did not get a response. We were extremely respectful and honestly this is just kind of ridiculous. We cannot think of anything that we did that warrants an extra fee. I love cats and I just suffered a miscarriage not even 2 weeks ago. My husband did this for me to get me out of the house and feeling better. Its not about the money but the deception. We were never warned during our visit or told we were breaking the rules. If they had made us aware of the charge, we could have better prepared, but instead it overdrafted our spending account resulting in an extra $50 in fees. I am extremely disappointed as this is the only cat cafe in Reno and I was excited to be able to interact with cats even though we can't adopt one right now. The cats seem well taken care of but this is not good business practice. We didn't even really feel like we could relax with the cats because the staff were almost hovering. They made conversation which was nice, but we were tip-toeing around trying not to make anyone or any of the cats uncomfortable. I am truly disappointed but we've agreed we won't be back.

Also, it seems the owner's only response to people with this same experience is that the policy was agreed upon multiple times. And she's right. But it is also very sneaky to act as though everything is fine and not mention a single thing to either of us and then charge us after we've left. We agreed to the policy because we thought if anything were to happen, they would at least speak up and warn us before immediately deciding to charge us with no warning. It seems like a money-grab considering how many people its happened to.

As I can't respond to the owner's comments directly but hopefully they see this. My husband and I were informed about all of the cats before interacting with them by the older employee. While she warned us that Duchess was temperamental/not the friendliest, we were not explicitly told not to approach her. That simply was not communicated. In fact, she told us that Duchess tends to be more friendly towards men!! Which is why he went to her in the first place. My husband was told twice that the cat had reached her limit. Saying multiple times makes it seem like it was higher. He was gentle and she did not lash out. He was not scratched or bitten. She was clearly not as stressed as you make it out to seem, she did not move from the exact position she was in when he approached her. I noticed you have cameras in the cat lounge so if you were not there to observe our visit, I suggest you look at the footage. The cat was perfectly fine after the interaction and so was he. The staff never once told him to stop, they said she had reached her limit. It's fine if that is what is considered a warning, but why not tell us we were going to be charged before we left? That is deceptive. They acted as if everything was perfectly fine. They never said we were breaking the rules. He did not intend to stress her out or harm her, that was clear. I'd understand the fee if he intentionally messed with her to piss her off, but that's just not what happened.

Enchanted Cat Cafe feels like a sanctuary for both feline enthusiasts and adoptable cats alike. From the moment you step inside, you're greeted by the employees and once you enter the cat portion, a sense of tranquility instantly washes away the stresses of the outside world.

The atmosphere is serene and calming, with soft ambient music playing in the background. Their drink options are varied from hot chocolate, coffee, many types of teas, and alcoholic beverage varieties.

But the true stars of the show are, of course, the cats. Roaming freely throughout the cafe, these furry residents exude an air of contentment, basking in the attention of visitors. From playful kittens to sweet and sleepy seniors, each cat has its own unique personality, making it impossible not to fall in love at first sight.

Whether you're a cat lover looking to make a new feline friend or simply seeking a new place to hang out, I highly recommend Enchanted Cat Cafe.

Even after the hour in the lounge is done, it was nice to sit in the cafe and catch up with friends.

Just grab a coffee elsewhere and go to the other shelters to visit, adopt, and make donations.
My mother and sister planned to go here for a visit. They dared to ask one question regarding shoes (yes, footwear is an issue here). They have a confusing flowchart about it. We emailed for clarification. The owners response was so rude that we decided to cancel. The cancellation policy shown just before you enter payment says 24 hour notice is needed. We cancelled 1 week and 1 day ahead of time. The owner has refused to refund us. Also, there is an additional $6.00 charge that the owner can't or won't explain and also won't refund.
I notified the owner that if we didn't receive a refund in full by 10am the next day, we would be refuting the charge as fraudulent with our bank. The owner then said I was being abusive and threatening and stopped responding.
This place has so many weird rules and policies, it's as if the owner would rather not have any customers all. For example, if you bring a kid that's 5 years old or younger, you must HOLD THEM the entire time, otherwise they will tack on additional charges.
The owner (or whomever I was speaking with) is obviously not a very experienced business owner and outright childish. You can't just make things up, gaslight people, and mess around with people's money.
Who knew dealing with a place called the "Kitty Cafe" would be such a nightmare.
To the owner: don't bother responding with any lies, I have screenshots of the conversation as well as your website and I'll post them here if I need to.
They also just hit the same account with a second charge while the initial charge was being disputed with the bank. The management at this place is deeply ineffective and fraudulent.

Chattanooga.name: Naughty Cat Cafe
Chattanooga.address: 3742 Tennessee Ave Suite 100, Chattanooga, TN 37409, USA

text.text:
What a wonderful experience !! They had approximately 40 cats in a couple of rooms. One room nicely decorated with couches and chairs and cat furniture. This room is a little dark on purpose. Fun to sit and let the cats come to you. There is a second room with full light and also lots of seating areas for cats and humans . Very clean! Amazingly friendly staff.
There are binders with all the cat information in case you like to adopt one.
Highly recommended activity to have fun and support a good cause!

We had never experienced a cat cafe before and I hope they are all as well done at the Naughty Cat Cafe! Several rooms full of cats to love on! Even a quiet room for the new residents to get used to their new lodgings. Highly recommend if you love cats. You will want to take them all home!

They have so many cats right now (12/13/2024)! All of them have so much personality and they‚Äôre sooooo soft! I came here with friends as a birthday gift to myself, I‚Äôm so glad I did. It is very calming sitting with the cats! They dim the lights and play soothing music while the cats just roam around. It is also extremely clean and the restroom smells great as well! They do provide binders all around the sitting area so you can learn about each cat, along with how to adopt one if you fall in love with one of the fur babies! As well as the cat petting, they provide you one free drink ‚Äî whether that be hot coffee, hot tea, soda, chocolate milk, or cold water! They also sell reasonably priced products, such as jewelry, cat toys, shot glasses, little pastries, and they even have cans of alcohol for sale (if that‚Äôs your thing!). I would 100% recommend this lovely place to anybody who even remotely enjoys cats! There are many different areas to sit, their one rule is to never pick up any of the cats.

Cat‚Äôs Cradle staff is friendly and knowledgeable. They have so many awesome cats ready to find their forever homes. We found our cat at Cat‚Äôs Cradle and couldn‚Äôt be happier. Highly recommend attending their open house to check out the kittens and cats up for adoption!
Great place and staff to match.  They are very knowledgeable and take their responsibilities seriously.  Will definitely pair you with a cat that wants to be in your home and heart.

They make sure your accommodated and allow you to take time with the cats. They take great care and also have a decent amount of volunteers! All the cats seem very well treated here and looked after.

I got Wonka and Veruca from them, didn't want to split the pair up, they already were very attached.

Absolutely love the Natural Per Center. I started shopping here a few years ago and won‚Äôt shop anywhere else. It‚Äôs very comforting to know that everything in store is truly safe for my pups. üê∂üêæ‚ù§Ô∏è
Great place to work.  I love that I can special order items that be don't carry in store.  Visiting with the Cat's Cradle Cats is an added bonus.
I adopted a cat here through Cats Cradle and it was great because I also got a bunch of free products like food and treats!

cafes.name: Pixeled Arcade and Beerhall
cafes.address: 1100 Northern Pacific Ave #101, Fargo, ND 58102, USA

text.text: I've been to this establishment multiple times and I have had good experiences but also negative. The last time I was there a few months ago, the ATM was down. The machines require coins. You cannot get coins without cash so we were unable to play games. When asking what options we had, the bartender was more preoccupied with working on their jewel art project than answering our questions. Sad, because we really enjoyed this place previously. Unimpressed.

This place is amazing! Talk about a nostalgic overload! The venue is packed with classic arcade machines and old school video games. The layout is exceptional and allows easy movement throughout the arcade. It never felt overcrowded even though the place was packed. The arcade machines were all in tip top shape and super well maintained, not an issue with a single one. I can‚Äôt believe it took us this long to come here. We will definitely be back many, many times!!!

This place is great! All the great arcade games from back in the day! Gen Xers will LOVE the nostalgia of it and younger folks will get a kick out of the ‚Äúvintage‚Äù games.  And for basically a quarter a game, you can‚Äôt go wrong! Then add tap beers and a few other beverage options; and it‚Äôs a great place to spend time.  Service was also great and friendly!  Wish I lived in the Fargo area so I could get there often.

Duluth.name: Wired Whisker
Duluth.address: 1823 E Superior St, Duluth, MN 55812, USA

text.text: I went there for the grand opening, and i absolutely love it. The baked goods and coffee are wonderful and being able to socialize with the cats makes this a purrfect destination for locals and tourists alike. Bear in mind that you do have to book a reservation to access the cat lounge, but it's super easy to do and very affordable on their website. Their cat roster does also change periodically since they work with animal rescues, and you may very well meet your new fuzzy best friend here.

Such an amazing place!! I actually didn't order any food or drink, but I did go into the kitty area! Ton of the cats were really interactive and wanted to sit on my lap. If you're looking to adopt, would highly recommend going here!! Kitties looked all so well taken care of!!

I cannot say anything about the adoption process, but visiting the cats on my birthday was a treat! I had a tea and a delicious cat-themed macaron. I was able to walk in, as no one had booked online, but had to wait about 15 minutes for the next hour to rollover (which I fully expected). The cats were mostly napping, but there was one who played a bit and then sat in my lap.

cafes.name: The Hillsboro Cafe
cafes.address: 3 N Main St, Hillsboro, ND 58045, USA

text.text: I don't go to small town restaurants often. I decided to go to The Hillsboro Cafe tonight. Let me tell you.... ABSOLUTELY amazing. I loved everything I ordered. I couldn't eat it all but I atleast had to try it and it's so good. The staff was so friendly and helpful. I am very happy with my orders. Thank you so much for the amazing service and the amazing food. Everything was absolutely amazing!!!!
Great small town atmosphere combined with top notch food. Be willing to travel miles for this absolute gem and you won't be disappointed. Their catering is on another level also.

If you find yourself on I29/81 between Fargo and Grand Forks save your hunger for the Hillsboro Cafe. The atmosphere is relaxing, service is spectacular and the food is outstanding. My husband ordered the Everything Omelette and I had the 1776 Burger and Wisconsin Cheese Soup. For later we purchased Scones from there assortment of baked goods.  Don‚Äôt forget to check out the wall of items you can purchase which includes the seasoning and sauce used on my burger.

Alexandria.name: Mount Purrnon Cat Caf√© + Wine Bar
Alexandria.address: 109 S Alfred St, Alexandria, VA 22314, USA

text.text: The cafe is such a great addition to the cat space, and it‚Äôs clear that the cats are well loved and taken care of. Some cats are seniors and just living out their last years in a bright, clean, lovely space, and others are much younger who are eager to make friends! The staff genuinely care about the cats and their care. Please stop by, support them and adopt!

MOUNT PURRNON CAT CAFE & WINE BAR has become a must-do for out of town kiddos visiting Northern Virginia, if you love cats and you love kiddies.

Mount Purrnon is located on Alfred Street just off King Street, the main 'drag' in Old Town Alexandria so everywhere you turn you are walking in historic footsteps. Parking is on the street. Payment is fed in to free standing rectangles. The receipt is placed on your car dashboard.

Mount Purrnon is a healthy walk towards the water with your back to the Metro. If you are lucky, you can catch Old Town's free trolley, a fun thing kids of all ages love to do. The trolley will land you near enough to the cafe allowing you to combine two kid fun events in one outing. ,

The Mount Purrnon Cafe is kitty corner to a vintage shop, around the cornerdown the street from Sephora and up the street from the amazing Torpedo Factory.

Entering Mount Purrnon Cat Cafe + Wine Bar, you enter the most delightful gift shop filled with cat 'stuff' of all types, high end, crafty and lower priced fun stuff, all benefiting the charity housed in this historic house once upon a time someone, maybe, infamous in history lived there, after all, ghosts of America's fathers still live there, technically.

Friendly volunteers sit waiting to take payment for adults, kids, lunch if you choose and the length of time your visit to last- 1/2 hour, an hour. I once met a young woman who pretty much spent all day there. She said she found inner peace.

Mount Purrnon profiles its current residents on the wall in this room so you sorta have an idea which kitties you will be greeted by upstairs AND maybe even want to take home with you if you are in the market for a furrever friend.

The stairs are a bit steep heading up to the cattery. There are steps outside, too.

Before you head up, there is a downstairs eating place with a limited menu that includes out of this world cheese melt sandwich a finicky-as-a-cat four year old I know literally inhales this sandwich. There is a cat themed bathroom on the first floor. It's sort of a nice thing to do- eat first, fill your tummy then head up the stairs.

The photos speak for themselves. I wanted to take them all but, got a better offer, two kiddos who love love love coming here to Mount Purrnon Cafe. Thank you, yet again.

oh yeah, photos are copyright (c) Carrie Devorah and may not be used unless given permission by me, not by google or the cafe

We had a wonderful time at Mount Purrnon! The staff was so helpful in answering our questions and they were informative of the cats. This business is doing wonderful things to support cats in the area. Will definitely be back!

Picked up some donuts to go very tasty and full of flavor! Highly recommend to anyone who hasn't been!

For the record I don't have any allergies or anything so for those interested I'm sure the staff are able to help you find a donut for you to enjoy!

Great place to drop by and grab some donuts. I used to come here back when the building used to be a Donut Hole. They have a good selection. I used to get all my donuts at Dan's Supermarket but after the rebrand into Family Fare they increased the price of their donuts and now it is just shy of the price here. Except the dough here is better. So now this is my new place for donuts

Bearscat was handing out Halloween coloring sheets to kids. They told my daughters that if they complete the coloring sheet they would get a free donut when they brought the sheet back in.  They were excited, colored the sheets over the weekend. We returned the sheets this morning and were told that they get a token for a free donut to use on their next visit. But that they would make an exception this time but not in the future. My 9 and 6 year old daughters looked up at me like what?  If you are going to have color contest and give out a donut to kids for participating.  GIVE THEM A DONUT, not some token to garner more business. It is terrible practice and i hope the owners consider changing this practice.

cafes.name: Peacock Alley
cafes.address: 422 E Main Ave, Bismarck, ND 58501, USA

text.text: We stopped in for the Downtown Burger Slam, the Dakota Grand Slam Burger is soooo good.  The burger is juicy & tasty.  Loved the Hot honey to drizzle as much as you like. It pairs well with the perfectly crunchy crispy bacon.  Love the bun too. The fries it comes with are yummy.  Ashton our server was friendly and he also suggested the smoke wings for political Wednesday wing night. Loved the smoky flavor and they are huge wings! You get your choice of dipping sauce, we loved the spicy ranch.  They also come with yummy fries.  Such a great dining experience.

Peacock Alley- The service was excellent‚Äîthe staff was attentive and friendly.  The food fell short, especially considering the prices. The menu prices didn‚Äôt match the final ticket, which was disappointing. The atmosphere had potential, but the experience was overshadowed by the loud music. It was so loud that everyone in the restaurant was shouting just to be heard, making it an uncomfortable environment for conversation. There‚Äôs room for improvement, especially in creating a more enjoyable dining ambiance.

This place is great if you want good quality food at a lukewarm temperature. We waited for an hour, watching all the lovely people around us getting their food even though they came in after us. However, we did have a reservation so they probably forgot about us. When we asked the server when our food would be ready because we had an event to get to in half an hour she assured us to stay because our food has been done but the chef won‚Äôt let it come out because his timing was off and didn‚Äôt get our meal done in one go. I personally find this hard to believe because I watched two of the tables around us get many parts of their meal separately. Overall, the lack of service from the incredibly crabby staff, fairly cold meal, and extreme wait while we watched other tables get food before us, is not worth the price of the restaurant.

Very sweet and helpful staff. All of the animals are well-cared for and in good, clean conditions. Their adoption process is thorough and has the animals' best intentions in mind, which I always love to see. We will definitely be back to check out more kitties as we look for a new furry friend!
Got a very beautiful kitty named Evelin she‚Äôs super happy and cuddly I am so glad they chose us as her forever home I couldn‚Äôt be happier

I would give full stars, our pup is amazing unfortunately he came with having worms in his stomach due to only getting one treatment he needed outta the 2. They do their best to keep the pups healthy we just got unlucky.

East Grand Forks.name: Bernie's
East Grand Forks.address: 121 Demers Ave, East Grand Forks, MN 56721, USA

text.text: I love this building and the interior. The staff wears aprons that appear to be period appropriate. The breakfast burrito tasted very fresh, natural, and satisfying. The coffee was good. The service was friendly providing recommendations. We did leave with a crookie. It was so delicious ü§§. Another reason to swing by East Grand Forks.

Tried for the first time and it was really good. Our server Josie was fantastic, friendly, and helpful. Tried out the leafe dog and was pleasantly surprised. The dog was split and grilled, and all the toppings complimented the dog nicely. The smorgasbord was well made and displayed. The strawberry jam, I believe was housemade and not overly sweet. The salmon was smoked perfectly, lots of flavor, but still juice. The cardamon soda was a big hit-refreshing. Really enjoyed the bake goodies, the tahini monster cookies was soft and flavorable and the pistachio rose muffin was devine. I do agree with the other reviewers, the prices are a bit high, but unique. Will try again.  SEPTEMBER 29th - Happy 2nd Birthday!  Breakfast was fantastic, and I really enjoyed the breakfast burrito. Made with leafse instead of a tortilla, a great crunch, and the salsa was perfect. The raspberry vanilla steamer and soda were tasty and refreshing.

Just love Bernie‚Äôs! Even the simplest sounding menu items are just so well made and full of fun flavors and textures! Friendly staff and such a comfy atmosphere. So many bakery items to take home and the store has amazing food items!

The husband , 2 kids and I came today 2/18 Sunday. It had been a few years since we‚Äôve been and remembered it being really good. It was very slow. First my husband ordered a double margarita and it was a single. Ordered a second one and it was just koolaid. So terribly sweet would‚Äôve given you a headache.  My husband ordered the picture. The two meat and two sides. We waited 30 minutes for our food. The two chicken tenders, day old mashed potatoes and one piece of sausage was 25 bucks and was ice cold. I ordered the Cajun shrimp platter and the shrimp was so tough it was as if it had been cooked the day before. Our bill for two mixed drinks, two sodas, a water and pretty terrible food was $106. And unfortunately the waitress wasn‚Äôt great. She didn‚Äôt come back to get plates for a long time and had to get up and ask for the check. I get that if you‚Äôre having a bad day, yeah it sucks. But the place was empty. Took the bartender 10 min to make one shot of us. We tip our waitress but the overall experience was disappointing for what we paid and the service experienced. Not sure what happened in the last few years but management and staff need to do better. Y‚Äôall would get a lot more business if the quality and cook of food was better and better service. We might try back in a few years if it‚Äôs even still in business

Placed a to go order # 32354206629740546 last night at the Williston Restaurant. Food was so bad I had to cook although I had just spent $65 for dinner. The only good part of the order was the corn bread. Like even the Mac N Cheese was horrible, the baked potato was by far the worst baked potato I have ever had, the corn wasn't edible, the pineapple slices were not good and the meat, the part FamousxDaves is supposed to be known for, each kind I ordered was just nasty. Super disappointing. I was so angry I couldn't even call the Restaurant because it wouldn't be fair to the girl who answered the phone what I had to say. I didn't want to cook, I had no choice.
Chopped pork sandwich was really good, but personal taste i didnt like the bbq sauce it was really sweet or the pickles. The fries though may be the best at any restraunt ever

Springfield.name: Eugene Springfield Cat Lounge
Springfield.address: 537 W Centennial Blvd, Springfield, OR 97477, USA

text.text: I stopped in to look around and check the scene out.  The owner was welcoming, happening, and just ever so stern.  These are live, young animals here.  Care must be taken for the welfare of all involved here.  The kids love visiting and playing with the cats.  The adults love visiting the cats, and the cats, most of all, love the giving and receiving of attentions.  $15.00 an hour, I believe.  Fun, fun,fun.

We recently adopted a kitten from here. We already love her more than words can tell.
I like going even though I have cats at home. The kittens have a wide range of personalities. Some lounge and love to be pet the whole time you're there. Others enjoy a mix of cuddles and play time. The best are the few who are rowdy and will play with anything. I suggest going when they first open. The kitties are waking up and ready to PLAY!!!!!!
Lots of cute cats! Playful, and adoptable, and they seem very well taken care of and watched over. Not too expensive for an hour slot, and they even let you in for free on your birthday!

Man, the last two weeks I had been struggling. My wife and I needed a good pick me up. We are so happy that we found this place. We've been in Fargo for a few months and we love downtown. But I needed a change from the wannabe hipster places. Rustica is much more my vibe.  Instead of chasing coolness, it's the inspiration for cool. Elegant but understated. Good lively crowd enjoying their evening without being obnoxious. My mocktail was so tasty and complex. The Spanish meatballs were savory with a small hint of sweetness. The buratta with tomatoes, so many hints of flavor. The French Farmer Pizza so to unique!  The whole staff was amazing. They were attentive but they you breathe. They all seemed to work well together, staying busy but never rushed. They didn't seem to hate their jobs, such a difference from most places.  This will be our go-to place now!

The food was fantastic. We ordered the airline chicken and bourbon glazed pork. Stunningly delicious. The mixed drinks were also fabulous. Highly recommend the spicy strawberry margarita and old fashioned.

Also, reservations are a MUST. We had them, but watched others get told there were no tables, as it‚Äôs not that big of a dining area in the main dining room. It‚Äôs well worth it - can‚Äôt wait to come back.
